Jackknife Estimates of Indirect Effect in a Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated Using the Vale and Maurelli (1983) Approach (Skewness = 2, Kurtosis = 7)

Source: R/vm_mod_complete_unstd_jack.R
vm_mod_jack.Rd

Jackknife Estimates of Indirect Effect in a Simple Mediation Model for Data Generated Using the Vale and Maurelli (1983) Approach (Skewness = 2, Kurtosis = 7)

vm_mod_jack(data, taskid)

Arguments

data

n by 3 matrix or data frame. data[, 1] correspond to values for x. data[, 2] correspond to values for m. data[, 3] correspond to values for y.
taskid

Numeric. Task ID.

See also

Other jackknife functions: beta_jack_simulation(), beta_jack_task(), beta_jack(), exp_jack_simulation(), exp_jack_task(), exp_jack(), jack(), mvn_jack_simulation(), mvn_jack_task(), mvn_jack(), mvn_std_jack_simulation(), mvn_std_jack_task(), mvn_std_jack(), vm_mod_jack_simulation(), vm_mod_jack_task(), vm_mod_std_jack_simulation(), vm_mod_std_jack_task(), vm_mod_std_jack(), vm_sev_jack_simulation(), vm_sev_jack_task(), vm_sev_jack(), vm_sev_std_jack_simulation(), vm_sev_std_jack_task(), vm_sev_std_jack()

Author

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

Examples

taskid <- 1
data <- vm_mod_dat(taskid = taskid)
vm_mod_jack(data = data, taskid = taskid)
